========== PLAN #1 ==========
[2026-02-16T08:27:26.457Z] {
  "plan": "# Plan: 2D Platformer Game — \"Platform Quest\"\n\n## Context\n\nBuild a self-contained 2D platformer from scratch in an empty project directory. The game targets web browsers using **Phaser 3 + TypeScript + Vite**. No external art assets — all visuals are generated programmatically using Phaser's Graphics API. The game features 5 levels with increasing difficulty, coin collecting, spike hazards, a lives system, and a scoring system.\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Phaser 3.90.0** — game framework (Arcade Physics)\n- **TypeScript 5.x** — language\n- **Vite 6.x** — dev server & bundler\n- No backend, no external assets, no Tiled maps\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\ntest_game/\n├── index.html\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vite.config.ts\n└── src/\n    ├── main.ts                  # Phaser GameConfig + entry point\n    ├── config/\n    │   └── gameConfig.ts        # Constants (dimensions, physics, colors)\n    ├── scenes/\n    │   ├── BootScene.ts         # Generate all textures from shapes\n    │   ├── MainMenuScene.ts     # Title screen\n    │   ├── GameScene.ts         # Core gameplay\n    │   ├── LevelCompleteScene.ts\n    │   └── GameOverScene.ts     # Game over + victory\n    ├── entities/\n    │   └── Player.ts            # Player movement, jump, death\n    ├── levels/\n    │   └── levelData.ts         # 5 level definitions as data\n    └── ui/\n        └── HUD.ts               # Score, lives, level overlay\n```\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### Step 1: Project Scaffolding\n- `npm init -y`, install `phaser@3.90.0`, dev deps `typescript`, `vite`\n- Create `tsconfig.json` (ES2020, ESNext modules, strict)\n- Create `vite.config.ts` (port 8080, auto-open)\n- Create `index.html` (centered canvas, loads `/src/main.ts`)\n\n### Step 2: Game Config + Entry Point\n- **`src/config/gameConfig.ts`** — constants: canvas 800x600, gravity 800, player speed 200, jump -450, 3 lives, color palette, texture key names\n- **`src/main.ts`** — `new Phaser.Game(config)` with Arcade physics, registers all 5 scenes\n\n### Step 3: Boot Scene (Asset Generation)\n- **`src/scenes/BootScene.ts`** — uses `this.add.graphics()` + `generateTexture()` to create:\n  - Player: 32x48 blue rectangle\n  - Platform: 128x32 brown block\n  - Ground: 64x32 tile (stretchable)\n  - Coin: 24x24 gold circle\n  - Hazard: 32x32 red triangle (spike)\n  - Exit: 40x56 green door\n- Then transitions to MainMenuScene\n\n### Step 4: Level Data\n- **`src/levels/levelData.ts`** — array of 5 `LevelDef` objects, each containing:\n  - `playerStart`, `platforms[]`, `coins[]`, `hazards[]`, `exit` positions\n  - Level 1: flat ground, no hazards (tutorial)\n  - Level 2: ground spikes introduced\n  - Level 3: gaps in floor\n  - Level 4: vertical climbing challenge\n  - Level 5: gauntlet with fragmented ground + many hazards\n\n### Step 5: Player Entity\n- **`src/entities/Player.ts`** — wraps `Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Sprite`\n  - Arrow keys: left/right movement, up to jump (only when `body.blocked.down`)\n  - `die()`: red tint + upward pop, `isOffScreen()` check for falling deaths\n  - `reset()` for respawning on same level\n\n### Step 6: HUD\n- **`src/ui/HUD.ts`** — three `Phaser.GameObjects.Text` elements (score, lives, level name)\n  - `setScrollFactor(0)` to stay fixed on screen\n  - Methods: `updateScore()`, `updateLives()`, `updateLevel()`\n\n### Step 7: Game Scene (Core Gameplay)\n- **`src/scenes/GameScene.ts`** — the integration point:\n  - `init(data)` receives level number, score, lives from scene transitions\n  - `create()`: builds platforms/coins/hazards/exit from level data, creates Player, sets up colliders\n  - Collisions: `physics.add.collider` (player↔platforms), `physics.add.overlap` (player↔coins/hazards/exit)\n  - Coin pickup: +10 score, disable coin body\n  - Hazard/fall: lose life, restart level or game over\n  - Exit: +50 bonus, advance to next level or victory screen\n\n### Step 8: Menu & Transition Scenes\n- **`MainMenuScene.ts`** — title \"PLATFORM QUEST\", blinking \"Press SPACE\" prompt\n- **`LevelCompleteScene.ts`** — shows level name cleared, score, \"Press SPACE for next level\"\n- **`GameOverScene.ts`** — \"GAME OVER\" or \"YOU WIN!\" based on victory flag, final score, restart option\n\n## Key Phaser APIs Used\n- `physics.add.staticGroup()` / `.create()` / `.refreshBody()` for platforms\n- `physics.add.sprite()` for player\n- `physics.add.collider()` / `physics.add.overlap()` for collisions\n- `graphics.generateTexture()` for programmatic assets\n- `scene.start()` / `scene.restart()` with data passing via `init()`\n- `input.keyboard.createCursorKeys()` for controls\n- `tweens.add()` for blinking text animation\n\n## Verification\n1. Run `npm run dev` — opens browser at `localhost:8080`\n2. Game loads through BootScene → MainMenuScene automatically\n3. Test checklist:\n   - Arrow keys move player, up jumps only when grounded\n   - Coins disappear on contact, score increases by 10\n   - Spikes kill player (red flash, life lost, level restarts)\n   - Falling off screen = death\n   - Reaching green door = level complete (+50 pts)\n   - All 5 levels progressively harder\n   - 0 lives = Game Over screen\n   - Completing level 5 = Victory screen\n   - SPACE on any end screen restarts appropriately\n4. Optional: set `arcade.debug: true` in main.ts to visualize physics bodies\n"
}
